To add slave or node to jenkins 
> security group of node - allow ssh from jenkins sg
> ssh to node 
# apt update && apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

> create a devops user on node
# mkdir /opt/jenkins
# chown devops: ubuntu /opt/jenkins/
# chmod 770 /opt/jenkins/
# ls -ld /opt/jenkins/
  drwxrwx--- 2 devops ubuntu 4096 Apr 6 13:21 /opt/jenkins/


> JENKINS
  > manage jenkins>add node 
                  > remote root dir -/opt/jenkins 
                  > add label
> usage -only build with label  
> lauch method - via ssh
> host - <private ip of node>
> add credential - user devops -passwword
> host key verification - enable non verification

## can also add key based ssh 
> same as above add credentials - ssh username with private key , add prvt key of node $cat Downloads/node-key.pem 


HOW TO USE THIS NODE OR SLAVE 
> configuration > restrict where this project run - add label mentioned while creating node
> select github repo path
> there is no maven installed on node 
    > add build step - invoke top level maven target - select maven3.9 installed on tools 


TO USE NODE ON PIPELINE 

> pipeline{
  agent{
        label '<label of node>'
       }
 }
